<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFE1FFCAFF8DFE41FD5AFCCE" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFE1FFCAFF8DFE41FE2CFC8E" blockId="59.[113,1089,423,926]" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFF8DFE41FF5CFE0E" bold="true" box="[113,226,423,446]" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE1FFCAFF16FE41FECFFE0E" author="BALY" box="[234,369,423,446]" firstAuthor="BALY" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" pagination="59 - 72" refId="ref47517" refString="BALY J. S. 1872: Descriptions of some species of Cassididae new to science. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1872: 59 - 72." type="journal article" year="1872">BALY (1872)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention how many specimens he had at his disposal and stated that the new species is ‘very closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFD5DFE21FCC9FE6E" authority=", Boh." authorityName="Boh." box="[673,887,455,478]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latevittata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFD5DFE21FC8DFE6E" box="[673,819,455,478]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">M. latevittata</emphasis>
, Boh.
</taxonomicName>
, and possibly only a variety of that species; differing principally in its transverse form, and in the absence of the reticulations…’. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE1FFCAFEABFDE1FE4DFDAE" author="SPAETH" box="[343,499,519,542]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" refId="ref50998" refString="SPAETH F. 1914: Chrysomelidae: 16. Cassidinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 62. W. Junk, Berlin, 180 pp." type="book" year="1914">SPAETH (1914)</bibRefCitation>
listed 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFDBCFDE1FD77FDAE" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1872" box="[576,713,519,542]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latissima">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFDBCFDE1FD77FDAE" box="[576,713,519,542]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">M. latissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as an aberration of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFC57FDE1FBFFFDAE" box="[939,1089,519,542]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latevittata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFC57FDE1FBFFFDAE" box="[939,1089,519,542]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">M. latevittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the taxon remained as its synonym until present (cf. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE1FFCAFD27FDC1FC2AFD8E" author="BOROWIEC" box="[731,916,551,574]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC 1999a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE1FFCAFC5AFDC1FBFEFD8E" author="BALY's" box="[934,1088,551,574]" firstAuthor="BALY's" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" pagination="59 - 72" refId="ref47517" refString="BALY J. S. 1872: Descriptions of some species of Cassididae new to science. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1872: 59 - 72." type="journal article" year="1872">BALYʼs (1872)</bibRefCitation>
statement is probably based on fact that he did not compare 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFCF6FDA1FC2FFDEE" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1872" box="[778,913,583,606]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latissima">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFCF6FDA1FC2FFDEE" box="[778,913,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">M. latissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with typical 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFBDFFDA1FF5EFDCE" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latevittata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFBDFFDA1FF5EFDCE" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">M. latevittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with broad pronotum but with the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFE1FFCAFDAAFD81FD15FDCE" box="[598,683,615,638]" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">syntype</typeStatus>
with narrow pronotum, here resolved as conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFEB8FD61FDAAFD2E" authorityName="Borowiec" authorityYear="1998" box="[324,532,647,670]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguineovittata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFEB8FD61FDAAFD2E" box="[324,532,647,670]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">S. sanguineovittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see remarks under 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFD11FD61FCC8FD2E" box="[749,886,647,670]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latevittata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFD11FD61FCC8FD2E" box="[749,886,647,670]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">S. latevittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Spaeth based the synonymy on the same population as he got the duplicate material from Balyʼs collection. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFF8DFD21FEA3FD6E" baseAuthorityName="Baly" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[113,285,711,734]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latissima">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFF8DFD21FEA3FD6E" box="[113,285,711,734]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">Stolas latissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is quite similar to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFE17FD21FD02FD6E" authorityName="Borowiec" authorityYear="1998" box="[491,700,711,734]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sanguineovittata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFE17FD21FD02FD6E" box="[491,700,711,734]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">S. sanguineovittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in simple erect vestiture on elytra while the latter has double vestiture formed by adherent and erect setae. I therefore restore species status of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFE86FCE1FE48FCAE" baseAuthorityName="Baly" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[378,502,775,798]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latissima">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFE86FCE1FE48FCAE" box="[378,502,775,798]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">S. latissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and designate 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFE1FFCAFD65FCE1FD43FCAE" box="[665,765,775,798]" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">lectotype</typeStatus>
from the BMNH specimen in order to conserve it status.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFE1FFCAFF6CFCA1FD5AFCCE" blockId="59.[113,1089,423,926]" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE1FFCAFF6CFCA1FE83FCEE" author="BOROWIEC" box="[144,317,839,862]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" pagination="119 - 251" refId="ref48151" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1996: Faunistic records of Neotropical Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne 65: 119 - 251." type="journal article" year="1996">BOROWIEC (1996</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE1FFCAFEBAFCA1FEC3FCEE" author="BOROWIEC" box="[326,381,839,862]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" journalOrPublisher="Genus" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" pagination="155 - 246" part="9" refId="ref48215" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1998 a: Review of the Cassidinae of Ecuador, with a description of thirteen new species. Genus 9: 155 - 246." title="Review of the Cassidinae of Ecuador, with a description of thirteen new species" type="journal article" year="1998">1998</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFE1FFCAFE7BFCA1FE00FCEE" author="BOROWIEC" box="[391,446,839,862]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" journalOrPublisher="Genus" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" pagination="43 - 138" part="13" refId="ref48380" refString="BOROWIEC L. 2002: New records of Neotropical Cassidinae, with description of three new species (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Genus 13: 43 - 138." title="New records of Neotropical Cassidinae, with description of three new species (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)" type="journal article" year="2002">2002</bibRefCitation>
) published several specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFC81FCA1FF04FCCE" authority="sensu Spaeth" authorityName="Spaeth" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latevittata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFC81FCA1FBBEFCEE" box="[893,1024,839,862]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">S. latevittata</emphasis>
sensu Spaeth
</taxonomicName>
which are most likely conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFE1FFCAFD9EFC81FD63FCCE" baseAuthorityName="Baly" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[610,733,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latissima">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFD9EFC81FD63FCCE" box="[610,733,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">S. latissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFE1FFCAFF8DFC61FC87FC2E" box="[113,825,903,926]" pageId="59" pageNumber="334" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFE1FFCAFF8DFC61FC87FC2E" blockId="59.[113,1089,423,926]" box="[113,825,903,926]" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFE1FFCAFF8DFC61FEBAFC2E" bold="true" box="[113,260,903,926]" pageId="59" pageNumber="334">Distribution.</emphasis>
